nodes.text: My son is allergic to peanuts.
PeanutAllergy(624): My son is allergic to peanuts.
Annot: My son is allergic to peanuts.
The last time we flew on an airline that served peanuts (Southwest) we called ahead and requested that no peanuts be served on our flight.
PeanutAllergy(624): The last time we flew on an airline that served peanuts (Southwest) we called ahead and requested that no peanuts be served on our flight.
Annot: The last time we flew on an airline that served peanuts (Southwest) we called ahead and requested that no peanuts be served on our flight.
The airline was extremely accommodating, but there were peanuts on the floor and between the seats from earlier flights.
PeanutAllergy(624): The airline was extremely accommodating, but there were peanuts on the floor and between the seats from earlier flights.
Annot: The airline was extremely accommodating, but there were peanuts on the floor and between the seats from earlier flights.
For that reason, I don't see banning peanuts on specific flights or a peanutfree buffer zone as real solutions.
PeanutAllergy(624): For that reason, I don't see banning peanuts on specific flights or a peanutfree buffer zone as real solutions.
Annot: For that reason, I don't see banning peanuts on specific flights or a peanutfree buffer zone as real solutions.
We now only fly airlines that don't serve peanuts.
PeanutAllergy(624): We now only fly airlines that don't serve peanuts.
Annot: We now only fly airlines that don't serve peanuts.
We're okay with Snickers because the peanuts are less likely to get spilled.
PeanutAllergy(624): We're okay with Snickers because the peanuts are less likely to get spilled.
Annot: We're okay with Snickers because the peanuts are less likely to get spilled.
However, this wouldn't be a good solution for those with an inhalation allergy.
PeanutAllergy(624): However, this wouldn't be a good solution for those with an inhalation allergy.
Annot: However, this wouldn't be a good solution for those with an inhalation allergy.
Maybe the ban could extend to all foods when there is a specific request.
PeanutAllergy(624): Maybe the ban could extend to all foods when there is a specific request.
Annot: Maybe the ban could extend to all foods when there is a specific request.
Since there's no reason to ban peanuts to begin with,
Mulder(533): Since there's no reason to ban peanuts to begin with,
Annot: Since there's no reason to ban peanuts to begin with,
the only thing you'd accomplish by banning all food is to have a large number of cranky, hungry passengers on longer flights.
Mulder(533): the only thing you'd accomplish by banning all food is to have a large number of cranky, hungry passengers on longer flights.
Annot: the only thing you'd accomplish by banning all food is to have a large number of cranky, hungry passengers on longer flights.
Not exactly a good way to engender customer loyalty or goodwill.
Mulder(533): Not exactly a good way to engender customer loyalty or goodwill.
Annot: Not exactly a good way to engender customer loyalty or goodwill.
I like peanuts,
mcs24(643): I like peanuts,
Annot: I like peanuts,
but I don't consider it my right to have airlines serve them to me.
mcs24(643): but I don't consider it my right to have airlines serve them to me.
Annot: but I don't consider it my right to have airlines serve them to me.
I don't think they need to.
mcs24(643): I don't think they need to.
Annot: I don't think they need to.
Plenty of times I'm not thrilled with what I am offered so I usually bring my own.
mcs24(643): Plenty of times I'm not thrilled with what I am offered so I usually bring my own.
Annot: Plenty of times I'm not thrilled with what I am offered so I usually bring my own.
I think some of this is just outrage that someone dare put a regulation on something.
mcs24(643): I think some of this is just outrage that someone dare put a regulation on something.
Annot: I think some of this is just outrage that someone dare put a regulation on something.
But I don't think passengers should be banned from bringing peanut products on the flight.
mcs24(643): But I don't think passengers should be banned from bringing peanut products on the flight.
Annot: But I don't think passengers should be banned from bringing peanut products on the flight.
There's a compromise that can be struck.
mcs24(643): There's a compromise that can be struck.
Annot: There's a compromise that can be struck.
I don't think there is anything wrong with banning airlines from serving bagged peanuts.
mcs24(643): I don't think there is anything wrong with banning airlines from serving bagged peanuts.
Annot: I don't think there is anything wrong with banning airlines from serving bagged peanuts.
It's an unnecessary risk
mcs24(643): It's an unnecessary risk
Annot: It's an unnecessary risk
and you'd think they would have caught onto that already.
mcs24(643): and you'd think they would have caught onto that already.
Annot: and you'd think they would have caught onto that already.
Banning passengers from bring their own peanut containing products (i.e. snickers or things with peanut oil) is probably too far,
mcs24(643): Banning passengers from bring their own peanut containing products (i.e. snickers or things with peanut oil) is probably too far,
Annot: Banning passengers from bring their own peanut containing products (i.e. snickers or things with peanut oil) is probably too far,
although peanut allergy people should be given the ability to not sit near that person.
mcs24(643): although peanut allergy people should be given the ability to not sit near that person.
Annot: although peanut allergy people should be given the ability to not sit near that person.
It seems like a fair compromise.
mcs24(643): It seems like a fair compromise.
Annot: It seems like a fair compromise.
There is indeed plenty wrong with the very idea that airlines should be banned from serving peanuts.
Mulder(533): There is indeed plenty wrong with the very idea that airlines should be banned from serving peanuts.
Annot: There is indeed plenty wrong with the very idea that airlines should be banned from serving peanuts.
Not only does it shift responsibility for the problems of a very small minority of people onto others,
Mulder(533): Not only does it shift responsibility for the problems of a very small minority of people onto others,
Annot: Not only does it shift responsibility for the problems of a very small minority of people onto others,
but it also accomplishes nothing, as peanuts and pieces of them are already onboard the aircraft.
Mulder(533): but it also accomplishes nothing, as peanuts and pieces of them are already onboard the aircraft.
Annot: but it also accomplishes nothing, as peanuts and pieces of them are already onboard the aircraft.
At the same time, there is negligible risk to peanut allergy sufferers,
Mulder(533): At the same time, there is negligible risk to peanut allergy sufferers,
Annot: At the same time, there is negligible risk to peanut allergy sufferers,
as evidenced by the data.
Mulder(533): as evidenced by the data.
Annot: as evidenced by the data.
There is indeed something wrong with banning peanuts on airlines.
Mulder(533): There is indeed something wrong with banning peanuts on airlines.
Annot: There is indeed something wrong with banning peanuts on airlines.
Despite the unfounded fears of certain death if they're exposed to peanuts,
Mulder(533): Despite the unfounded fears of certain death if they're exposed to peanuts,
Annot: Despite the unfounded fears of certain death if they're exposed to peanuts,
no one has died from anaphylaxis from exposure to peanuts, peanut dust, or peanut oil onboard a U.S. airliner.
Mulder(533): no one has died from anaphylaxis from exposure to peanuts, peanut dust, or peanut oil onboard a U.S. airliner.
Annot: no one has died from anaphylaxis from exposure to peanuts, peanut dust, or peanut oil onboard a U.S. airliner.
Are we talking about airlines not providing peanuts, or peanuts not being allowed on an airplane?
mcs24(643): Are we talking about airlines not providing peanuts, or peanuts not being allowed on an airplane?
Annot: Are we talking about airlines not providing peanuts, or peanuts not being allowed on an airplane?
These are two VERY different issues.
mcs24(643): These are two VERY different issues.
Annot: These are two VERY different issues.
I would be indifferent to rules preventing airlines from serving peanuts
mcs24(643): I would be indifferent to rules preventing airlines from serving peanuts
Annot: I would be indifferent to rules preventing airlines from serving peanuts
(actually, I would welcome it, because I like the crackers better!).
mcs24(643): (actually, I would welcome it, because I like the crackers better!).
Annot: (actually, I would welcome it, because I like the crackers better!).
People who want peanuts can bring their own, easily enough.
mcs24(643): People who want peanuts can bring their own, easily enough.
Annot: People who want peanuts can bring their own, easily enough.
Should people be banned from bringing their own peanuts?  No.
mcs24(643): Should people be banned from bringing their own peanuts?  No.
Annot: Should people be banned from bringing their own peanuts?  No.
And honestly, people would be more effective using market forces to convince airlines to change their menus.
mcs24(643): And honestly, people would be more effective using market forces to convince airlines to change their menus.
Annot: And honestly, people would be more effective using market forces to convince airlines to change their menus.
I do have a cousin who legitimately goes into anaphylactic shock at exposure to peanuts.
mcs24(643): I do have a cousin who legitimately goes into anaphylactic shock at exposure to peanuts.
Annot: I do have a cousin who legitimately goes into anaphylactic shock at exposure to peanuts.
It's not a joking matter;
mcs24(643): It's not a joking matter;
Annot: It's not a joking matter;
I would guess we have fewer complications because people with peanut issues don't fly.
mcs24(643): I would guess we have fewer complications because people with peanut issues don't fly.
Annot: I would guess we have fewer complications because people with peanut issues don't fly.
But this is a minority,
mcs24(643): But this is a minority,
Annot: But this is a minority,
and I would not support a ban on peanuts existing on an airplane.
mcs24(643): and I would not support a ban on peanuts existing on an airplane.
Annot: and I would not support a ban on peanuts existing on an airplane.
but do we really need airlines to serve peanuts?
mcs24(643): but do we really need airlines to serve peanuts?
Annot: but do we really need airlines to serve peanuts?
This reaction isn't actually about peanuts at all.
mcs24(643): This reaction isn't actually about peanuts at all.
Annot: This reaction isn't actually about peanuts at all.
your son flew with peanuts wedged in the seat and on floor . . . and was fine?
Alex412(757): your son flew with peanuts wedged in the seat and on floor . . . and was fine?
Annot: your son flew with peanuts wedged in the seat and on floor . . . and was fine?
Assuming he's not going to eat a peanut off the floor or someone's seat, I don't see why you feel the need to have peanuts banned.
Alex412(757): Assuming he's not going to eat a peanut off the floor or someone's seat, I don't see why you feel the need to have peanuts banned.
Annot: Assuming he's not going to eat a peanut off the floor or someone's seat, I don't see why you feel the need to have peanuts banned.
Your son obviously can handle the flight.
Alex412(757): Your son obviously can handle the flight.
Annot: Your son obviously can handle the flight.
